aristaAclMIB.name: aristaAclMIB

revisions.description: Revised to correct a syntax error, limit the size of ACL names in INDEXes to match the maximum OID length, and make columns used in INDEXes not-accessible. This last change is not backwards-compatible.

aristaAclMIB.contactinfo: Arista Networks, Inc. Postal: 5453 Great America Parkway Santa Clara, CA 95054 Tel: +1 408 547-5500 E-mail: snmp@arista.com
aristaAclMIB.description: The MIB module for managing Access Control Lists (ACLs) on Arista devices.

AristaAclRuleAction.name: AristaAclRuleAction
AristaAclRuleAction.description: Action associated with an ACL rule. If the action has value 'remark(2)', then only the remark field of the ACL rule is meaningful; all other fields are don't-cares.

AristaAclRangeOperator.name: AristaAclRangeOperator
AristaAclRangeOperator.description: Range operator used by an ACL rule.

aristaAclDpSupportFlags.name: aristaAclDpSupportFlags
aristaAclDpSupportFlags.description: This attribute describes the data-plane ACL support matrix. If data-plane ACLs are supported, the acl bit is 1; otherwise, other bits are 0. If data-plane ACLs are supported, the logging, counter and routerAcl bits indicate whether the data plane supports those features for ACLs.

aristaIpAclTable.name: aristaIpAclTable
aristaIpAclTable.description: A table that contains IP ACLs that are configured on the switch.

aristaIpAclEntry.name: aristaIpAclEntry
aristaIpAclEntry.description: Information about a specific IP ACL that is configured on the switch.

aristaIpAclName.name: aristaIpAclName
aristaIpAclName.description: The name of the IP ACL.

aristaIpAclReadOnly.name: aristaIpAclReadOnly
aristaIpAclReadOnly.description: This attribute has value 'true(1)' if the IP ACL is configured as read-only; otherwise, the value is 'false(2)'.

aristaIpAclStatsEnabled.name: aristaIpAclStatsEnabled
aristaIpAclStatsEnabled.description: This attribute has value 'true(1)' if the IP ACL is configured to have per-rule statistics enabled; otherwise, the value is 'false(2)'.

aristaIpAclCountersIncomplete.name: aristaIpAclCountersIncomplete
aristaIpAclCountersIncomplete.description: This attribute has value 'true(1)' if the IP ACL has incomplete counter; otherwise, the value is 'false(2)'.

aristaIpAclRuleTable.name: aristaIpAclRuleTable
aristaIpAclRuleTable.description: A table that contains IP ACL rules that are configured on the switch.

aristaIpAclRuleEntry.name: aristaIpAclRuleEntry
aristaIpAclRuleEntry.description: Configuration information about a specific IP ACL rule.

aristaIpAclRuleSeqId.name: aristaIpAclRuleSeqId
aristaIpAclRuleSeqId.description: This attribute is the sequence ID for this ACL rule.

aristaIpAclRuleProto.name: aristaIpAclRuleProto
aristaIpAclRuleProto.description: This attribute is the IP protocol to be matched by this ACL rule. The value 0 indicates the rule matches any IP protocol.

aristaIpAclRuleSrc.name: aristaIpAclRuleSrc
aristaIpAclRuleSrc.description: This attribute is the IP source address to be matched by this ACL rule, subject to the aristaIpAclRuleSrcMask value.

aristaIpAclRuleSrcMask.name: aristaIpAclRuleSrcMask
aristaIpAclRuleSrcMask.description: This attribute is the IP source-address mask in this ACL rule. For the source address of the packet to match the rule, the bitwise logical-AND of the address and this mask must be equal to the value of aristaIpAclRuleSrc.

aristaIpAclRuleDest.name: aristaIpAclRuleDest
aristaIpAclRuleDest.description: This attribute is the IP destination address to be matched by this ACL rule, subject to the aristaIpAclRuleDestMask value.

aristaIpAclRuleDestMask.name: aristaIpAclRuleDestMask
aristaIpAclRuleDestMask.description: This attribute is the IP destination-address mask in this ACL rule. For the destination address of the packet to match the rule, the bitwise logical-AND of the address and this mask must be equal to the value of aristaIpAclRuleDest.

aristaIpAclRuleL4PortSrcOper.name: aristaIpAclRuleL4PortSrcOper
aristaIpAclRuleL4PortSrcOper.description: This attribute determines TCP/UDP source-port matching behavior in this ACL rule. If this attribute has value 'any(0)', then attribute aristaIpAclRuleL4PortsSrc is ignored.

aristaIpAclRuleL4PortsSrc.name: aristaIpAclRuleL4PortsSrc
aristaIpAclRuleL4PortsSrc.description: This attribute is a list of TCP/UDP source ports to be matched in this ACL rule. They are represented as decimal strings, separated by spaces. A maximum of 10 ports is allowed. Attribute aristaIpAclRuleL4PortSrcOper determines how the source ports are matched in this ACL rule.

aristaIpAclRuleL4PortDestOper.name: aristaIpAclRuleL4PortDestOper
aristaIpAclRuleL4PortDestOper.description: This attribute determines TCP/UDP destination-port matching behavior in this ACL rule. If this attribute has value 'any(0)', then attribute aristaIpAclRuleL4PortsDest is ignored.

aristaIpAclRuleL4PortsDest.name: aristaIpAclRuleL4PortsDest
aristaIpAclRuleL4PortsDest.description: This attribute is a list of TCP/UDP destination ports to be matched in this ACL rule. They are represented as decimal strings, separated by spaces. A maximum of 10 ports is allowed. Attribute aristaIpAclRuleL4PortDestOper determines how the destination ports are matched in this ACL rule.

aristaIpAclRuleTtlOper.name: aristaIpAclRuleTtlOper
aristaIpAclRuleTtlOper.description: This attribute is the IP TTL (Time To Live) operation code used in this ACL rule. Combined with attribute aristaIpAclRuleTtl, it specifies the IP TTL matching behavior in this ACL rule.

aristaIpAclRuleTtl.name: aristaIpAclRuleTtl
aristaIpAclRuleTtl.description: This attribute is the IP TTL value in this ACL rule. Attribute aristaIpAclRuleTtlOper determines how the TTL values is matched in this ACL rule.

aristaIpAclRuleTracked.name: aristaIpAclRuleTracked
aristaIpAclRuleTracked.description: This attribute has the value 'true(1)' if this ACL rule is tracked; otherwise, the value is 'false(2)'. A tracked rule matches packets in existing ICMP/UDP/TCP connections.

aristaIpAclRuleFragments.name: aristaIpAclRuleFragments
aristaIpAclRuleFragments.description: This attribute has value 'true(1)' if this ACL rule is configured to match IP fragments; otherwise, the value is 'false(2)'.

aristaIpAclRuleTcpFlags.name: aristaIpAclRuleTcpFlags
aristaIpAclRuleTcpFlags.description: This attribute describes TCP flags that are matched by this ACL rule.

aristaIpAclRuleEstablished.name: aristaIpAclRuleEstablished
aristaIpAclRuleEstablished.description: This attribute has value 'true(1)' if this ACL rule matches existing TCP connections; otherwise, the value is 'false(2)'.

aristaIpAclRuleIcmpType.name: aristaIpAclRuleIcmpType
aristaIpAclRuleIcmpType.description: This attribute is the ICMP type that is matched by this ACL rule. The attribute is ignored in the ACL rule if the value is 65535.

aristaIpAclRuleIcmpCode.name: aristaIpAclRuleIcmpCode
aristaIpAclRuleIcmpCode.description: This attribute is the ICMP code that is matched by this ACL rule. The attribute is ignored in the ACL rule if the value is 65535.

aristaIpAclRuleAction.name: aristaIpAclRuleAction
aristaIpAclRuleAction.description: This attribute is the action applied to this ACL rule.

aristaIpAclRuleLog.name: aristaIpAclRuleLog
aristaIpAclRuleLog.description: This attribute has value 'true(1)' if logging is required in this ACL rule; otherwise, the value is 'false(2)'.

aristaIpAclRuleRemark.name: aristaIpAclRuleRemark
aristaIpAclRuleRemark.description: This attribute is the remark string applied to this ACL rule.

aristaIpAclRuleStatsTable.name: aristaIpAclRuleStatsTable
aristaIpAclRuleStatsTable.description: A table that contains statistics for IP ACL rules.

aristaIpAclRuleStatsEntry.name: aristaIpAclRuleStatsEntry
aristaIpAclRuleStatsEntry.description: Statistics for a specific IP ACL rules.

aristaIpAclRuleTimeMark.name: aristaIpAclRuleTimeMark
aristaIpAclRuleTimeMark.description: A TimeFilter for this entry. See the TimeFilter textual convention to see how this works.

aristaIpAclRuleStatsPktCount.name: aristaIpAclRuleStatsPktCount
aristaIpAclRuleStatsPktCount.description: This attribute is the number of packets that this ACL rule matched.

aristaIpAclRuleStatsLastUpdateTime.name: aristaIpAclRuleStatsLastUpdateTime
aristaIpAclRuleStatsLastUpdateTime.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time the aristaIpAclRuleStatsPktCount was last updated for this ACL rule.

aristaMacAclTable.name: aristaMacAclTable

aristaMacAclEntry.name: aristaMacAclEntry
aristaMacAclEntry.description: Information about a specific MAC ACL that is configured on the switch.

aristaMacAclReadOnly.name: aristaMacAclReadOnly
aristaMacAclReadOnly.description: This attribute has value 'true(1)' if the MAC ACL is configured as read-only; otherwise, the value is 'false(2)'.

aristaMacAclStatsEnabled.name: aristaMacAclStatsEnabled
aristaMacAclStatsEnabled.description: This attribute has value 'true(1)' if the MAC ACL is configured to have per-entry statistics enabled; otherwise, the value is 'false(2)'.

aristaMacAclCountersIncomplete.name: aristaMacAclCountersIncomplete
aristaMacAclCountersIncomplete.description: This attribute has value 'true(1)' if the MAC ACL has incomplete counter statistics; otherwise, the value is 'false(2)'.

aristaMacAclRuleTable.name: aristaMacAclRuleTable
aristaMacAclRuleTable.description: A table that contains MAC ACL rules that are configured on the switch.

aristaMacAclRuleEntry.name: aristaMacAclRuleEntry
aristaMacAclRuleEntry.description: Configuration information about a specific MAC ACL rule.

aristaMacAclRuleSeqId.name: aristaMacAclRuleSeqId
aristaMacAclRuleSeqId.description: This attribute is the sequence ID for this ACL rule.

aristaMacAclRuleSrc.name: aristaMacAclRuleSrc
aristaMacAclRuleSrc.description: This attribute is the MAC source address to be matched by this ACL rule, subject to the aristaMacAclRuleSrcMask value.

aristaMacAclRuleSrcMask.name: aristaMacAclRuleSrcMask
aristaMacAclRuleSrcMask.description: This attribute is the MAC source-address mask in this ACL rule. For the source address of the packet to match the rule, the bitwise logical-AND of the address and this mask must be equal to the value of aristaMacAclRuleSrc.

aristaMacAclRuleDest.name: aristaMacAclRuleDest
aristaMacAclRuleDest.description: This attribute is the MAC destination address to be matched by this ACL rule, subject to the aristaMacAclRuleSrcMask value.

aristaMacAclRuleDestMask.name: aristaMacAclRuleDestMask
aristaMacAclRuleDestMask.description: This attribute is the MAC destination-address mask in this ACL rule. For the destination address of the packet to match the rule, the bitwise logical-AND of the address and this mask must be equal to the value of aristaMacAclRuleDest.

aristaMacAclRuleProto.name: aristaMacAclRuleProto
aristaMacAclRuleProto.description: This attribute is the MAC protocol number to be matched by this ACL rule. The protocol value 4294967295 (0xFFFFFFFF) is a value that indicates the rule matches any protocol.

aristaMacAclRuleAction.name: aristaMacAclRuleAction
aristaMacAclRuleAction.description: This attribute is the action applied to this ACL rule.

aristaMacAclRuleLog.name: aristaMacAclRuleLog
aristaMacAclRuleLog.description: This attribute has value 'true(1)' if logging is required in this ACL rule; otherwise, the value is 'false(2)'.

aristaMacAclRuleRemark.name: aristaMacAclRuleRemark
aristaMacAclRuleRemark.description: This attribute is the remark string applied to this ACL rule.

aristaMacAclRuleStatsTable.name: aristaMacAclRuleStatsTable
aristaMacAclRuleStatsTable.description: A table that contains statistics information for MAC ACL rules.

aristaMacAclRuleTimeMark.name: aristaMacAclRuleTimeMark
aristaMacAclRuleTimeMark.description: A TimeFilter for this entry. See the TimeFilter textual convention to see how this works.

aristaMacAclRuleStatsPktCount.name: aristaMacAclRuleStatsPktCount
aristaMacAclRuleStatsPktCount.description: This attribute is the number of packets that this ACL rule matched.

aristaMacAclRuleStatsLastUpdateTime.name: aristaMacAclRuleStatsLastUpdateTime
aristaMacAclRuleStatsLastUpdateTime.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time the aristaMacAclRuleStatsPktCount was last updated for this ACL rule.

aristaIpv6AclTable.name: aristaIpv6AclTable

aristaIpv6AclEntry.name: aristaIpv6AclEntry
aristaIpv6AclEntry.description: Information about a specific IPv6 ACL that is configured on the switch.

aristaIpv6AclName.name: aristaIpv6AclName
aristaIpv6AclName.description: The name of the IPv6 ACL.

aristaIpv6AclReadOnly.name: aristaIpv6AclReadOnly

aristaIpv6AclCountersIncomplete.name: aristaIpv6AclCountersIncomplete

aristaIpv6AclRuleTable.name: aristaIpv6AclRuleTable
aristaIpv6AclRuleTable.description: A table that contains IPv6 ACL rules that are configured on the switch.

aristaIpv6AclRuleEntry.name: aristaIpv6AclRuleEntry
aristaIpv6AclRuleEntry.description: Configuration information about a specific IPv6 ACL rule.

aristaIpv6AclRuleSeqId.name: aristaIpv6AclRuleSeqId
aristaIpv6AclRuleSeqId.description: This attribute is the sequence ID for this ACL rule.

aristaIpv6AclRuleProto.name: aristaIpv6AclRuleProto
aristaIpv6AclRuleProto.description: This attribute is the IPv6 upper layer protocol to be matched by this ACL rule. The value 0 indicates the rule matches any IPv6 protocol.

aristaIpv6AclRuleSrc.name: aristaIpv6AclRuleSrc
aristaIpv6AclRuleSrc.description: This attribute is the IPv6 source address to be matched by this ACL rule, subject to the aristaIpv6AclRuleSrcMask value.

aristaIpv6AclRuleSrcMask.name: aristaIpv6AclRuleSrcMask
aristaIpv6AclRuleSrcMask.description: This attribute is the IPv6 source-address mask in this ACL rule. For the source address of the packet to match the rule, the bitwise logical-AND of the address and this mask must be equal to the value of aristaIpv6AclRuleSrc.

aristaIpv6AclRuleDest.name: aristaIpv6AclRuleDest
aristaIpv6AclRuleDest.description: This attribute is the IPv6 destination address to be matched by this ACL rule, subject to the aristaIpv6AclRuleDestMask value.

aristaIpv6AclRuleDestMask.name: aristaIpv6AclRuleDestMask
aristaIpv6AclRuleDestMask.description: This attribute is the IPv6 destination-address mask in this ACL rule. For the destination address of the packet to match the rule, the bitwise logical-AND of the address and this mask must be equal to the value of aristaIpv6AclRuleDest.

aristaIpv6AclRuleL4PortSrcOper.name: aristaIpv6AclRuleL4PortSrcOper
aristaIpv6AclRuleL4PortSrcOper.description: This attribute determines TCP/UDP source-port matching behavior in this ACL rule. If this attribute has value 'any(0)', then attribute aristaIpv6AclRuleL4PortsSrc is ignored.

aristaIpv6AclRuleL4PortsSrc.name: aristaIpv6AclRuleL4PortsSrc
aristaIpv6AclRuleL4PortsSrc.description: This attribute is a list of TCP/UDP source ports to be matched in this ACL rule. They are represented as decimal strings, separated by spaces. A maximum of 10 ports is allowed. Attribute aristaIpv6AclRuleL4PortSrcOper determines how the source ports are matched in this ACL rule.

aristaIpv6AclRuleL4PortDestOper.name: aristaIpv6AclRuleL4PortDestOper
aristaIpv6AclRuleL4PortDestOper.description: This attribute determines TCP/UDP destination-port matching behavior in this ACL rule. If this attribute has value 'any(0)', then attribute aristaIpv6AclRuleL4PortsDest is ignored.

aristaIpv6AclRuleL4PortsDest.name: aristaIpv6AclRuleL4PortsDest
aristaIpv6AclRuleL4PortsDest.description: This attribute is a list of TCP/UDP destination ports to be matched in this ACL rule. They are represented as decimal strings, separated by spaces. A maximum of 10 ports is allowed. Attribute aristaIpv6AclRuleL4PortDestOper determines how the destination ports are matched in this ACL rule.

aristaIpv6AclRuleHopLimitOper.name: aristaIpv6AclRuleHopLimitOper
aristaIpv6AclRuleHopLimitOper.description: This attribute is the IPv6 Hop Limit operation code used in this ACL rule. Combined with attribute aristaIpv6AclRuleHopLimit, it specifies the IPv6 Hop Limit matching behavior in this ACL rule.

aristaIpv6AclRuleHopLimit.name: aristaIpv6AclRuleHopLimit
aristaIpv6AclRuleHopLimit.description: This attribute is the IPv6 Hop Limit value in this ACL rule. Attribute aristaIpv6AclRuleHopLimitOper determines how the Hop Limit values is matched in this ACL rule.

aristaIpv6AclRuleTcpFlags.name: aristaIpv6AclRuleTcpFlags
aristaIpv6AclRuleTcpFlags.description: This attribute describes TCP flags that are matched by this ACL rule.

aristaIpv6AclRuleEstablished.name: aristaIpv6AclRuleEstablished
aristaIpv6AclRuleEstablished.description: This attribute has value 'true(1)' if this ACL rule matches existing TCP connections; otherwise, the value is 'false(2)'.

aristaIpv6AclRuleIcmpType.name: aristaIpv6AclRuleIcmpType
aristaIpv6AclRuleIcmpType.description: This attribute is the ICMP type that is matched by this ACL rule. The attribute is ignored in the ACL rule if the value is 65535.

aristaIpv6AclRuleIcmpCode.name: aristaIpv6AclRuleIcmpCode
aristaIpv6AclRuleIcmpCode.description: This attribute is the ICMP code that is matched by this ACL rule. The attribute is ignored in the ACL rule if the value is 65535.

aristaIpv6AclRuleAction.name: aristaIpv6AclRuleAction
aristaIpv6AclRuleAction.description: This attribute is the action applied to this ACL rule.

aristaIpv6AclRuleRemark.name: aristaIpv6AclRuleRemark
aristaIpv6AclRuleRemark.description: This attribute is the remark string applied to this ACL rule.

aristaIpv6AclRuleStatsTable.name: aristaIpv6AclRuleStatsTable
aristaIpv6AclRuleStatsTable.description: A table that contains statistics information for IPv6 ACL rules.

aristaIpv6AclRuleTimeMark.name: aristaIpv6AclRuleTimeMark
aristaIpv6AclRuleTimeMark.description: A TimeFilter for this entry. See the TimeFilter textual convention to see how this works.

aristaIpv6AclRuleStatsPktCount.name: aristaIpv6AclRuleStatsPktCount
aristaIpv6AclRuleStatsPktCount.description: This attribute is the number of packets that this ACL rule matched.

aristaIpv6AclRuleStatsLastUpdateTime.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time the aristaIpv6AclRuleStatsPktCount was last updated for this ACL rule.
